==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: catecholamine
<hw>catecholamine</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>catechol</ets> +
<ets>amine</ets>.]</ety> <def>any of a group of chemicals including
epinephrine and norepinephrine that are produced in the medulla of the
adrenal gland. They function as neurotransmitters in the sympathetic
nervous system. Also, any structurally related chemical substance,
whether natural or synthetic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

